"The fact is a lot of people” have already done a variety of innovations on standalone solar power for wifi

Vickram Crishna notes that many if not all, of the wifi routers within the [http://drupal.airjaldi.com/ AirJaldi] network are solar-powered. If you are interested, I can send you some nice pictures, taken when I went with the Tibtec team to service one of the very remote routers, on a hilltop, completely standalone.

There is also the [[Green WiFi]] [http://www.green-wifi.org/] effort started by Bruce Balkie that has sought to promote solar + wifi in various wireless applications around the world."
(http://blog.onevillage.tv/?p=743)


